                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="aga_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a type of British cooker made of solid iron that is also used for heating. <span class="def_qt"><span class="wrap">‘</span>Aga saga<span class="wrap">’</span></span> is a humorous name for a novel about the lives of British middle-class women, because <span class="dh">Agas</span> are very popular with this group.</span></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="aga_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">1930s: from the Swedish name <span class="ei">(Svenskaa) A(ktiebolaget) Ga(sackumulator)</span> ‘Swedish Gas Accumulator Company’, the original manufacturer.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
